The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, July 5: Almost 55 lakh central government employees will now be able to choose a date to draw their new pay scale under the Sixth Pay Commission award. According to an office memorandum, the Centre today allowed its employees time till December to fix the base date for taking the new pay scale.                             
	 New Delhi, July 5: The National Textiles Corporation (NTC) has done away with the system of inviting tenders for selling lands of its closed mills and adopted the e-auction route, which is more transparent.                             
	 New Delhi, July 5: The finance ministry today said food inflation, which fell steeply by almost 4 percentage points during the third week of June, would take some time to come down to an acceptable level of 5-6 per cent.                             
	 New Delhi, July 5: Indias apparel export, impacted by the recent debt crisis in Europe, dropped by an annual 6.8 per cent to $820 million in May. The slump in garment export was in contrast to about 35 per cent growth in the countrys total outward consignments.                             
	 New Delhi, July 5: The group of ministers, which is reviewing the recovery path of Air India, will meet next month to discuss the infusion of Rs 1,200 crore as equity and also review the steps taken by it to turn around.
                                                                                                                          
